The paper deals with designing efficient algorithms for processing large amounts of data in distributed processing frameworks, which is a problem in the field of distributed computing. The paper specifically focuses on problems such as Matrix Multiplication, 3-SUM, and All Pairs Shortest Paths, which are problems in the field of algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with the trade-offs between memory and number of machines, which is a problem in the field of distributed computing and parallel algorithms, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves analyzing the efficiency of algorithms, which is a problem in the field of theoretical computer science, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
